{"word":"σοβαρός","slug":"σοβαρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σοβαρός</b></el> <el>(σοβᾰρός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σοβέω'><el>σοβέω</el></a>\n<p/>properly, <i>scaring birds away: —</i> and so,<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>rushing, rapid</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ρῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>swaggering, pompous, haughty</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; of a horse, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ρῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>; also <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}